messages.content: "Uwaaa!" I let out a sleepy noise as I stretch, getting up from bed and heading to the common area we would all be meeting at. Probably, anyways.
There’s only really 1 area, it’s not a big cabin.
I spring to my feet. Unless I’m the one who took the last shift or whatever.
I awake.
"Good morning, all."
"Good morning indeed…"
"Did you all have a restful sleep?"
"Mmmgh." I mutter, rubbing my eyes.
"Hoho… I’ve had pleasant dreams."
"Glad to hear, Doug." I sigh. "Another day, another door." I look to everyone. "Any plans for after the doors?"
“…Might try to hunt, I guess? I don’t know if we need to eat here, even…”
"I will say, I haven't felt particularly hungry yet... *buuuut* I also haven't exactly been working up an appetite!" I pop my 'p's in the last word for emphasis.
"I can help with uh, whatever."
"I'll help with hunting after the doors, yes. Would be nice to find some solid salt, too, though, that's a secondary concern."
“Salt???”
"...do you want to eat *unseasoned* meat?"
"Do you plan to head to the birth door today, Celine?"
"We could always boil the seawater, right? It would condense down to salt."
//gonna let scipe reply given the awkward timing on those responses in succession
“If I have to. Good luck summoning salt out of this incomprehensible place, but at least if I’m looking for animals they’d be pretty easy to spot.”
Am I Celine? “Yeah, I guess I’ll go there.”
"I'll be heading there first, as well. Ruthilia's plan could work, if we attempted it..."
I side-eye 17, then back to Cyrus. "No need to bother with Ruthilia anymore, I suppose. My name is Celine, as my father has so graciously revealed."
"...wait, really? He's been calling us all by the names of his kids."
"That's the thing with the old man. A broken clock is right twice a day."
"Hoho… So little confidence."
“…Your father?”
"What?"
"Yes, my father." I take a moment, thinking about how to go about it. "Well, not biological. I was an orphan, and he was the headmaster. I feel like that's good enough, right?"
“…This was also the case for me.”
"Ah. Well, that explains a bit."
The old man just smiles.
“And Roshan, even if they’ll deny it.”
"That makes three of us, then."
“Bizarre…”
Okay, whatever, cool. They have dads.
I have a dad. I don't think they have to know that though.
"Well. What about you, Sixe- Azura?"
"What *about* me?"
"What are you going to do?"
"Um, I'll just help someone with something." *Don't leave me alone.*
"...well, if you go into that door-" I point to the Growth door. "-, me and Yazmine could come pick you up after we're done with our doors."
"I don't. Really want to?"
“…I mean, you gotta if you want to get out of here.”
"You have to, though. We need to go through them to be able to leave this place."
“But I guess if you’re not in a rush…”
"It's not that I don't want to get out of here, I just. We don't have any p-proof that it'll work, so..."
*Ugh. You sound so stupid. Desperate.*
“There’s… plenty of time in the day even with the doors. I, um… Guess I’ll see you guys in a bit, after I’m birthed.”
"Have fun being born."
"It's the only way we *have*, however. If you'd just prefer company, I can wait until Yaz is done and keep you company."
“Mhm. Haha! Yeah.”
“What??? Oh. Is that—I see, that would be… if she wants…”
"I could also stick around if you'd like, but I'd hate to intrude."

*Ugh. Why are you so obvious about it? Can they immediately tell what I want? Not to be left alone? Are they going to use it against me? That must be it. Why else would they give a fuck. They've figured out that I'm f-fucking insane and gross or whatever from all that, and now they're trying to look in on my life like voyeurs for proof.*
"No, actually, you know what? It's fine. You're right. I have to do it eventually. Might as well just do it."
"I don't need anyone to hold my hand through it. Ha-ha. Ha."
“Mm! Well. That’s good. Good luck. With that.”
I smile. She took my lessons well.
"Well, if you're sure. We'll be back for you afterwards."
"Yep. I'm sure. Mhm. Yep."
"I'll just... see you guys? Later?"
"Of course, Azura. We'll see you later."
"Yes." I get up to go to the Birth door.
I go with him, also.
I also leave.
In the direction of the birth door?
No, the growth door.
((The growth door is inside the house))
o rite
I go.. through it? I guess?

"You have reached the door of growth. The blooming flower of your life into what it should have been. You are not tainted by any other door yet today.  Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #056, is to enter while no one else on this island is inside. This is your isolation." It opens.
I enter.
Seeing as everyone else is heading off to find doors, I go to see if I can track one down myself.
I walk to the Birth door.
"Shall we go?" Douglas looks at Celine.
"We might as well."
He goes with Cyrus as well.
((are we just. all still together then i was waiting for the channel switches to settle))
((Yes))
I run my fingers through my hair. “Graaaagh!! Stupid, damn… pretty little coward, eurgh…”
"...do you mean Azura?"

“Yes!!! Why can’t people just say what they mean???? I’m not saying we should be fuckin’ interrogating her like that one asshole, but… I mean what’s, supposed to be the conclusion, there?? Of that whole display?”

"...well. Hm. Reading people is a skill you develop, and even then, it's still hard to properly understand someone you barely know." I cross my arms as we walk. "But, if what I've talked with her serves me well... she's afraid of seeming weak. Easy prey for those around her."
“Then??? Get stronger?????”
The old man laughs.
"If it were that simple, she would have no reason to be afraid, I'd say."
"I think she's forgotten much of her past life. If she could awaken those memories, perhaps she'd see she is not as weak as she feels."
“Hmph. Maybe. Could just as easily do worse, though.”
I sigh. "Either way, it isn't any of our busi- wait, did you say she's pretty?"
"Well, I mean, lots of boys and girls are pretty. It's more of an objective fact than a subjective opinion. I was quite the cute child."

"Some say I’m quite pretty myself, hoho!" 17.

L is waiting for them at the village, casually waving a severed human leg to say hello.
"...what is that."
"...why does he...?" I sigh, closing my eyes and rubbing at my temple. "It's gonna be a long day, isn't it?"
“Well, I don’t know about objective, b—” Oh, that’s gore.
"Apparently the wolf ate a guy last night." L.
"...sayonara, oomf-chan." I murmur as quietly as possible, before returning to speaking tone. "And why would he do that?"
"What?"
“What?”
"Dunno. I wasn’t around. I just met him with blood around his mouth and he told me it was from this. Could’ve been making out with it, I guess." L.
“Huh?! Wh—where did he go??”
"That... does sound more like him."
"Off towards the beach." L points in that direction casually.
"...huh. How... I just. Cannot see Johammad doing that." I scratch my head, thinking on this. How peculiar.
Regardless. "If you all would like to check on him, that is fine. I'd still prefer to go through my door first, however.
“Was he alone?!”
"I would be fine with going to see him alone if neither of you want to come. Though, I'd always prefer the company."
“…Better be a stupid fuckin’ waste of my time swear to god damn hell it all…” I run to the beach.
Actually, 60 and 64 just arrive here anyway. Daryush is back as well.
johammad stirs in his sleep in a manner that indicates he’s having a pleasant dresm
64 mumbles and twitches, seeming to be stuck in a nightmare. "No... mmm... I... I'm sorry... Daryush..."
The 2 wake up to the smell of blood.

"Mmmmnnn..."

...oh, right! I was asleep. Right! Right. And not only that, I wake up to something most odd. "F- Fours? You're still here?"
I loosen my arms around them a little.
"I, um. What? No, I don't..." I push myself off of him roughly, suddenly claustrophobic in my half-awake state.
"Y-yeah. I'm... here. What's g-going on?" I look around the room blearily.
Mohammad’s snout is covered in relatively fresh blood. The blood is most likely from the random severed leg laying near his bed.

Oh. I guess I loosen my arms around them entirely... "N- no, no, everything should be fine, I was just surprised that that was real, you know? Or if it was real, that maybe you'd slipped away overnight, because you realized I'm big and smelly or something like that."
I slowly sit up, and rub my eyes.
My breath catches in my throat. "Wh... what the fuck? What the fuck, John? What did you do?"
I fall off the bed, landing hard in the blood from the leg. "Aghh! What... what??"
I pull myself up and try to stumble my way out of the cabin. I need to... I need to get it off me.
I need to get to the water.

"What's wrong?! What's happening?!" Suddenly feeling very awake, I rush to my feet, and look around the room. Oh... oh gosh, no. Is that what that smell is? No, no, no, that can't be... how could somebody have... that doesn't...
I fall to my knees. I can barely see the leg through the tears. I guess that makes them a self-defense mechanism?
I try to follow after Fours.
You’re headed for the beach then?
"I- I don't know why I didn't hear anything! I'm sorry! I would've protected them if I could've!"
"No! No! Stay there! I... just... please... please stay."
I leave.
((Channel split))
"...okay!!" I guess I'm staying with the horrible bloody severed mangled leg!
You’re alone.

I throw up on the floor near the cabin entrance, and try to wipe away the tears, but for some reason, they just keep coming and coming and coming and coming, even though this is REALLY a situation where everyone could use your strength and-
I go back. To the bedroom. To look at the leg, and all that.
What's it like? Does it still have its, um... its clothes, or a shoe, or something like that? Was it obviously severed by a blade?
((Roll medicine)) It has a shoe.
You can’t tell what did this.
Okay. Okay.
"You slept here." Ebrahim’s voice reaches out to you from the door.

I freeze. No, no, no. It's so obvious what he's going to do here, and I'm not going to be able to push back against it, because it's technically possible that I'm responsible for what's happened, and it wouldn't be very nice to throw the possibility out. "...I did."
"I see." He looks at the leg. "So Cyrus was telling the truth then…"
"A... about what?"
"He saw a vanishing pile of bodies in my home last night. Along with… The vanished retribution door."
"...is this your home?"
"I'm sorry."
"No. But if it existed, it would have had to end up somewhere." He sighs. "Not that I wanted you to use this home either."
"...I was... sleepy. I'm really, really sorry."
I slowly turn around and try to leave the building.
He lets you walk out. "Well… It’s not as though you could’ve made things worse, I suppose."
"...Y- yeah."
I look around. Outside. Is anyone else around?
I instinctively wipe my mouth with my forearm.
Just you 2.
I sit down in the grass and do nothing.
For, um. A while, I guess.
Until something happens!!!!!
"What are you doing?"
"I don't know."
"I feel awful."
"So does everyone."
"That's sad. I wish they didn't."
He’s silent for a moment. Then he turns around and walks away.
I just sit here. Not thinking. Or not trying to think? It's hard to literally think not one single thing when you saw the body of a person you ruthlessly and brutally killed dead and then some.
I wait for a little bit longer.
"Undercooked breakfast, did you?" L shows up, unfortunately.
I look at him, my brow knit. What’s that even supposed to mean? "I... um, I don't think I ate."
"Then what’s with the blood?"

"The blood? I mean, um... somebody died... i- in there..." I point to the cabin. "Though I don't see how that would... how that would..."

Oh, oh God no. I gag, and double over, and try to vomit again. Probably only acid left in there. My throat burns horribly.
"Someone important?"
"I don't know! I don't know I don't know I don't know I don't know, okay!? Look for yourself! There's only a leg left! Go see if you recognize the hair on it!"
I run towards the beach.

"Huh." L.

Roshan is talking to 34.
((channel switch?))
((Yes))
He’s at the beach.

I rub my snout until I'm positive there's no blood left. How do I know? I don't know! Maybe there's some part of me that unconsciously gets how much scrubbing it takes to get bloodstains out of fur. Haha. This is so awful. I'm disgusting. I wouldn't do that. Why would I even joke about that? Only because it's secretly not a joke, and everyone is going to find out what a horrific excuse for a person you are. May as well give up and start calling yourself a beast.
I get out of the water before a wave can put me out of my misery. I fall back on the sand and wait for the sun to bake all the water out of my fur and clothes.
Roshan and 34 approach.
Headed to the beach?
Yeah. I need to not be covered in... this.
I hurry to the water, mind blank. Once I reach it, I essentially fall in. Is it warm, cold? Well, I don't care.
Is it, though?
There’s a bloodstained stone door on the beach.
I take note of it. But that's not really at the top of my priority list right now.
The sight of the blood on it does incline me to turn away, though.

I right myself, and start scrubbing at the stains on my skin and shirt. The saltwater isn't doing much, but I got to it before it dried, which is helping. I grab some a handful of sand and use it as a sort of makeshift sponge.
After a while of this, I start thinking.

There aren't many ways to interpret this, right? He... I know the way this is going to go. He said he didn't hear what happened, or something. He won't ever admit to this. I know him. But... hearing isn't the issue. He had blood covering his face. I know there are deep sleepers out there, but... getting liquid splashed onto your face is one of the notable ways to get through to any of them. It's just... not a good story.
What did I even expect? Getting comfortable with the sharpest-toothed thing on this godforsaken island. It's almost funny.
I start involuntarily giggling, before clamping my teeth down and stopping myself.

I guess, well, the question is who it was. Who was he willing to do this to... and then... just get back into bed with me? No attempt to clean it up, nothing. The denial only came when he saw how shocked I was. Up until that, he was acting totally normal. Did he really just not even know that... that murder is wrong? Or, that it's upsetting?
That's not true. I'm pretty sure that's not true, at least. It would have just... been that it was somebody he needed to do this for. Or, he felt he needed to do it. I don't know.
But then, why the denial? Did he just need more time to explain? Did I make him rush?
I... god, I didn't even give him a chance to get a word out, did I? Shit. I... maybe it wouldn't have meant anything. And I don't think I was wrong to be fucking freaked out!
Didn't even clean his damn snout first.

But I think... he deserves a chance. I've been with him long enough now to trust that he generally knows when to give in to his instincts and when not to. I owe him a shot. And... I just... I don't like being out here alone. It's making me feel... bad. Unwhole. Like I don't know where to point myself.
And the door seems to be staring at my neck.

I take a final sweep at my clothes. The bloodstains are still visible, but I could probably pass them off to the other people as just food stains. I mean, food stains could be bloodstains too, anyways. I'm not vegan.

Finally trudging out of the water and up the beach, I slowly start down the path back to the cabin. I'm taking my time. I consider sharpening a stick or something, but I doubt it would do much good against Jo. We've got quite the size difference going.
Haha.
Do you mean the village?
I believed that the village was made up of cabins.
Yes.
There’s the old man’s cabin separately.
Daryush approaches you on the way back. "Good... You’re okay."
Huh?
I blink, trying to clear my eyes.
"I didn’t see you at all yesterday."
"Y... yeah."
I twitch slightly.
"This is going to sound weird, but what's your name, again?"
"…Daryush. I went through the birth door with A- Uh, the one you’d know as 56… yesterday."
I bristle. "No, you didn't. I've kept very good track of which people went into which doors in my head. What number are you, again? Huh?"
"But… Yes I did? You can ask her."
My head is pounding. Did that happen? Or, better question, is asking him going to help me figure out if it did? I guess I just... need to talk to 56, maybe.
"Y-yeah. I... sorry. I guess I got confused."
"I don't mean to be aggressive."
"Sorry."
Johammad runs in this direction.
Can I not deal with one thing at a time?
((what would you call the buildings in the village if not cabins then. for future reference. houses?))
((They are cabins but generally I say houses yeah))
"…Huh."
"I don't... that's..."
I rub my forehead.
"Okay, look, why are you calling yourself Daryush now? What did you get from the birth door?"
"…Nothing worth talking about. But everyone else knows my name now. No reason not to go by it."
Alright. Good. It's not him yet.
"Is it okay if I just call you 34 for now."
"Sure."
"Cool. Awesome. Let's... go see what's going on with Jo, 34."
"I promise he's not as scary as he looks."
"Alright." He follows.
I tentatively head to wherever the wolf is by now.
Johammad is laying in the sand.
"Good… You’re alive too."
I dash past them, and throw myself into the water.
I gag on the saltwater. It's a better feeling in my throat than what was there before, which isn't saying much, but I need this.
I scrub feverishly over every part of my body that's exposed. My nails are sharp. I'd rather have my own blood on my fur than *theirs*, if that's what it comes to.
((They’re not on the beach anymore so I guess channel split again? Johammad just ran past))
((lol sure))
((drive by))
"Hhhhhh- hi." Whew. That took more effort than I expected to get out. Guess I was breathing heavier than I thought, haha.
"Are... are you okay?"
"Yes? I think 64 was more worried about *you*."
I gesture at the person speaking. "You remember 34, right, Jo?"
"Y... yeah."
I keep breathing.
"Okay. So, do you want to explain to him why you ran past us like that?"

"...Huh? Well, um... that lovely fellow back there, L, he pointed out to me that... my face... funny thing, was covered in blood! So I threw up. And my throat felt like it was gonna melt. And, and... if I didn't get it all out, I felt like..." I pause. "I don't know what I felt like."
I wait for him to continue.
"Ugh… That guy."
I stare up at the sky.
"...Is it still there? Did I get all the blood?"
"It just blends into your fur. Don't worry about that."
"Could you tell 34 where the blood came from, Jo?"
"I don't know. I probably ate a guy. That seems to be the most feasible explanation?"
"What!?"

"I don't think I'd do that. P- personally. But the... I don't know. What Dad said at least seems to imply that they'd already be dead by the time I got to them? Maybe... maybe that makes it better? Like, my wolf instincts kicked in...?"
I look visibly disgusted at the word 'probably'. "You don't remember?"
"Not at all. I thought I was just... you know. There. With you."
"Doing... regular sleep stuff..."
"I- it's not your fault if you're disgusted! I guess it's possible that I really am that horrifically disgusting after all, haha."

I consider this, stopping myself from cringing back from him. This world... the one that we exist in. Normally, I would just think he was lying. But one thing has been true so far - we forget the sins we've committed until the time is right to recall them. Could this just be... another cruel trick of Ismalisa?
"I... it's okay, Jo. If it's not my fault that I'm disgusted, then this probably isn't your fault, either. I understand."
"But... try not to do it again. Please. For my sake."
I walk over and give him a tentative pat on the shoulder.
Man, he's tall.
"I promise I won't, okay? I promise... I would never... I don't want to..."
I rise off of the sand.
"If I eat another person, then you have permission to kill me, okay? It's a promise."
I sigh.
"I saw another door on the beach just now. Do you want to go check it out?"
"Where?" 34 looks around. There is indeed no door.
"I... okay, yeah." I get to my feet. "Let's go do that."
"I, um..." Hm. I try to look around for the trail in the sand I would have left when I rushed down here. Is it still around?
You’re around that same area. If there was a door here you’d see it.
I head into the water, around where I was before. Maybe it's only visible from there?
I follow loosely behind Fours...?
"I swear it was here a second ago."

...

"Maybe I ate the door too?"
I choke. "Wh-what? That wouldn't... I think I'd be able to see the outline of it in your belly, Jo!" I start laughing.
...I feel my stomach, to make sure it's not suspiciously door-shaped.

It is not. 

"A door vanished? I’ve… Heard about this before. The retribution door vanished from the mountain a long time ago."
"Well, maybe it's only here at certain times of day?"
"Like, it switches between the mountain and the beach in intervals, or something."
"Maybe." I scratch my head. "Not like it was destroyed, right? There'd be some evidence left behind, like a bunch of wood chunks, surely..."
"It was made of stone, actually."
"And it was... hm."
"It was bloodstained. This is going to sound dumb, but... maybe it only shows up if you have blood on your skin?"
"Might make sense for something called the 'retribution' door."
"Right?" I look to Jo.
"That's... hm, maybe." I try to remember if I saw a door on my way here.
With a completely casual expression, 34 slices a knife into his own palm. "Hm… Still not seeing anything. Maybe it’s about being alone?"
I look away uncomfortably. "Um, were there any more details in that story about the door?"
"When it was on the mountain, I mean."
"You’d have to ask the chief, unfortunately."
...I look up at the sky. But I actually pay attention this time. What time is it? Did we sleep through the night?
It’s morning.
"M... maybe we just don't worry about it for now, and go through the door in the village, or something?"
I swish my hand in the water of indeterminate temperature. "That seems like as good a plan as any."
"Sure. Let's go. As long as we don't forget about this one."
"Um, do you need anything for that cut, by the way, 34?"
"Yeah, okay. I'll keep it in mind for you. I'll keep it so firmly in mind that all the other bad thoughts can't get in."
"Good to hear." I give him a thumbs up.
"I’m fine. It’s just a scratch." He does heal himself though.
I head back to the village.
I follow.
For clarification everyone except 56 is there. L and 17 are also here.
"Oh, um- hi, everyone!"
“Oh, okay. At least…” I shake my head. “Did you eat a guy!?”
"I just don't think that's the case."
"It's not out of the question."
"So you’re betting on made out with a severed leg?" L.
"Are you truly a wild beast, then?" 17.
"I've got 20 bucks on him trying to get with it."
"Like a wild hyena! I know, not the right dog, but..."
"I hope I'm not, haha. But it's hard to argue with waking up with blood on your lips and a severed leg in the room."
"How do you plan to hunt that many bucks? I've only seen a few deer." L.
“Did you have sex with a leg and or my brother??? These would be better than the eating thing I guess!!”
"I see. Well, that at least partly convinces me you did not do it."
"I'm sorry! I know it's disgusting. You might have to kill me if things get worse, but Fours already has that covered."
None of this is helpful.
“Woke up…? Would anyone have tried to… frame a…”
"CAN YOU ALL PLEASE SHUT UP!" I yell.
I contemplate legs.
"Well, I believe in you, J-" I stop.
Meep.
I was already done speaking, anyway.
"Jeez, wrong side of the cot this morning?" L doesn’t shut up, unlike the other NPCs.

"We're not here to talk about legs! We're not here to talk about Jo! There is nothing you are going to learn from him, because he doesn't remember it. There is nothing you are going to gain from HARASSING him, because he already doesn't want to be violent! I understand being afraid, given that we're all trapped on a fucking ISLAND together, but that doesn't mean you start speculating about having SEX with a LEG!!" I stare at Sylvia on that last beat.
"Now, we're going to enter the door. Okay??"
“You might not give a shit about anything, but I want to live! So yes, it *does* matter if one of us killed someone in cold blood.”
I ignore her, and look around for the door.

I shrug. "It was likely not him, anyway. There's already quite a lot of prejudice against Johammad, and it'd be easy to blame such a thing on him. He's not a wild beast without control." I say this simply, as if me already believing it makes it true.

I then go to the Birth door myself.

I'm... glad. I'm glad they shouted like that.

"Do... do you think it would be a worse sin if I ate a person, or just kissed their leg? I- I mean, ideally, it's neither, but which would be worse?"
I go to the door, because unlike Roshan, I’m not enough of a moron to have forgotten where its clearly visible location out in the open is.
"...I think you're still a good person either way, John. You don't remember doing either thing, right?"
I see the door instantaneously, and brush ahead of Sylvia to reach it first.
"I don't, I swear..."
I sit back and wait for everyone who plans to enter to do so.
"Then no one in their right mind should have any issue with you."
"Well... except for the person who that leg belonged to, I guess. They might."
"...I think they were already dead anyways? So it shouldn't even make a difference to them, haha. Unless their ghost is around..."
“It…. Yeah, there was only a leg. I don’t think it’s feasible to swallow all the rest…” I turn up quickly to Mohammad. “…They? You know who it was?”
"...No. Do you?"
"How could him saying 'they' possibly indicate that he knew who it was?" I'm not looking at her while I say this.
I try to enter the door.
“What I mean is, why do you think they were already dead? …Did you encounter an intact body, pass out, and then wake up like that?”

"Um... my- my dad... the leader, I mean, he said that... someone else told him there were a bunch of dead bodies in his house? But... they disappeared, so he seems to think the leg we found was part of one of them..."
“…I see. I get where you’re coming from, then…”

"You have reached the door of birth. The seeds of what made you you, forever, in the center of the world. You are not tainted by any other door yet today. Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #064, is none." The door opens for 64.
"There wasn't anyone else around when me and Fours fell asleep..."
“…I guess I don’t care if it turns out you eat corpses.” I contemplate this a bit before coming to a conclusion.
"Don’t we all eat corpses?" 17 makes some wise analysis.
"Not if you're a vegan."
“You always know just what to say, gramps.”
"I hope I don't corpses..." I approach the door.
I wait until Fours is done on the door to attempt to open it.
I am in the door.
Who’s next?
Me.
I want to hear what the door has to say to me.

"You have reached the door of birth. The seeds of what made you you, forever, in the center of the world. You are not tainted by any other door yet today. Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #057, is none." The door opens for 57.
I go in.
Who’s next?
Me!!!

"You have reached the door of birth. The seeds of what made you you, forever, in the center of the world. You are not tainted by any other door yet today. Your requirement to open this door, Inmate #060, is to enter with Inmate #001 at the same time." The door speaks as you try to open it.
"Well, that's unfortunate."
But he was in the last memory I had, too, and I don't remember him needing to be there with me... um...
He isn't around, is he?
I don't think he is.
